hopobject.body: What do you study? kamagra oral jelly for sale in durban It is not, he admits, normal practice in Norway for photographs of authors to adorn the front covers of their paperbacks. Does this rock star-cum-novelist feel that, more than most writers, he is a brand? “Yeah I am, I am. And I don’t mind that, I realise that is what you become. But my daughter grew up with me being a well-known man, and I remember she would say that there was a picture of Jo Nesbø in the papers today, not Dad. And she said it 'Jo-Nesbø’, like it’s one word. And that’s how I see it: Jo-Nesbø is the brand, and I’m the guy who is a dad or a brother or a bandmate.”
